-- Goldman hires Morgan Stanley veteran Michael Wise: report
-- 
-- Tue Aug 10, 2010 4:58am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/08/10/us-goldman-wise-idUSTRE67915X20100810

 

 BANGALORE  (Reuters) - Goldman Sachs Group Inc ( GS.N ) has hired Michael Wise, a Morgan Stanley ( MS.N ) veteran, to run its financial institutions group, the Wall Street Journal said. 

 Wise has worked at Morgan Stanley for 13 years and was most recently the chairman of its equity capital-markets division and a co-head of equity capital markets in the Americas, the business daily said. Financial institutions group is a part of Goldman's equity capital markets group, Wall Street said. Michael Wise, who will also become a Goldman partner, succeeds Stuart Bernstein, who is moving to the New York-based company's investment-banking group to head its clean technology and renewable-energy companies group, the paper said. Goldman Sachs could not immediately be reached for comment by Reuters outside regular U.S. business hours. (Reporting by Archana Shankar in Bangalore; Editing by Erica Billingham)